## ── PROJECT IDENTITY ───────────────────────────────────────────────
App: MathScript: Ultimate Quest
Type: Gamified math learning web app for kids
Status: MIGRATING — Replit (Python FastAPI) → Oracle Cloud (Spring Boot Java)
Current backend: Python FastAPI (port 5000)
Target backend: Spring Boot Java (port 8080)
Frontend: React 18 + Vite (JavaScript, no TypeScript)
Database: PostgreSQL — was Neon/Replit, now Oracle DB or self-hosted Postgres on Oracle VM
Payments: Stripe
AI APIs: Google Gemini 2.5 Flash (storytelling + images), OpenAI o4-mini (math solver), ElevenLabs (TTS)
Deploy: Oracle Cloud VM (Ubuntu/Oracle Linux), systemd services, Nginx reverse proxy

## ── CRITICAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES ─────────────────────────────────
# These MUST be set in the Oracle VM environment or .env file.
# NEVER hardcode these values. Always use os.environ.get() or @Value in Java.
Required env vars:
  DATABASE_URL        # postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/dbname
  GEMINI_API_KEY      # Google Gemini API key
  OPENAI_API_KEY      # OpenAI API key
  ELEVENLABS_API_KEY  # ElevenLabs TTS key
  STRIPE_SECRET_KEY   # Stripe secret key
  STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET # Stripe webhook signing secret
  STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY # Stripe publishable key
  SESSION_SECRET      # HMAC session signing secret (min 32 chars)

## ── KNOWN MIGRATION ISSUES TO FIX ──────────────────────────────────
ISSUE 1 — Database connection:
  - Old: Replit Neon PostgreSQL (via REPLIT_DB or DATABASE_URL auto-set)
  - Fix: Set DATABASE_URL manually on Oracle VM
  - DB falls back to in-memory if DATABASE_URL is missing (see database.py)
  - Action: Always check if DATABASE_URL is set before blaming other bugs

ISSUE 2 — Port mismatch:
  - FastAPI runs on port 5000 by default
  - Vite dev proxy in vite.config.js points to http://localhost:8000
  - Fix: Update vite.config.js proxy to port 5000 for Python, or 8080 for Spring Java

ISSUE 3 — Stripe replit connector:
  - Old: Replit Stripe connector auto-injected credentials
  - Fix: Set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY manually as env vars

ISSUE 4 — CORS origins:
  - Old: Replit auto-set allowed origins
  - Fix: Update CORS middleware in backend/main.py with Oracle VM public IP or domain

ISSUE 5 — Static file serving:
  - FastAPI serves React build from frontend/dist
  - Ensure build runs before start: `cd frontend && npm run build`
  - Path: app.mount("/", StaticFiles(directory="frontend/dist"))

ISSUE 6 — Systemd / process persistence:
  - Replit kept app alive automatically
  - Oracle: must use systemd service or screen/tmux to keep alive
  - SSH keepalive: ServerAliveInterval 60, ServerAliveCountMax 10

## ── ARCHITECTURE RULES ──────────────────────────────────────────────
1. Session IDs: always pattern sess_[a-z0-9]{6,20}, validated with HMAC signing
2. Never expose API keys to the frontend — all AI calls go through backend
3. Database operations must handle fallback to in-memory mode gracefully
4. All user input must be validated/sanitized before passing to AI or SQL
5. Stripe webhooks must verify signature using STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
6. CORS: never use wildcard "*" in production — explicitly list allowed origins

## ── FRONTEND RULES (React + Vite) ──────────────────────────────────
Tech: React 18, Vite, GSAP (animations), no TypeScript, JavaScript ES2022
State: useState/useCallback/useEffect (no Redux — keep it simple)
API calls: all go through frontend/src/api/client.js — never call fetch() directly
Routing: manual state machine in App.jsx (no React Router)
Styling: inline styles with CSS-in-JS style objects + global styles injected in App.jsx
Fonts: Orbitron (game-font), Rajdhani, Inter — loaded from Google Fonts
Build output: frontend/dist/
Key components:
  - App.jsx: routing state machine, session management
  - pages/Quest.jsx: main game loop
  - pages/Onboarding.jsx: hero select + welcome
  - components/AnimatedScene.jsx: GSAP hero battle animations
  - components/MiniGame.jsx: interactive mini-games
  - components/ShopPanel.jsx: item shop
  - components/ParentDashboard.jsx: parent view + PDF export
  - components/SubscriptionPanel.jsx: Stripe checkout UI

Frontend error patterns:
  - "Cannot read properties of undefined" → check API response shape before rendering
  - Blank screen → check vite dev server proxy config, check if FastAPI is running
  - GSAP animation not playing → check ref is attached, check gsap.context cleanup
  - Session not persisting → check localStorage in getOrCreateSessionId()
  - Image not loading → check Gemini image generation endpoint, check base64 data URI

## ── BACKEND RULES (Python FastAPI — current) ───────────────────────
Tech: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, Uvicorn, psycopg2, pydantic v2
Entry: backend/main.py
DB: backend/database.py (PostgreSQL with in-memory fallback)
Run: uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5000
Imports: use `from backend.X import Y` — not relative imports
HMAC session: sign_session_id() / verify_session_id() — never skip verification

Backend error patterns:
  - ImportError backend.database → run from project root, not from backend/
  - psycopg2 OperationalError → DATABASE_URL not set or wrong credentials
  - 422 Unprocessable Entity → pydantic validation failed, check request body schema
  - 500 on /api/story → likely GEMINI_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY missing
  - CORS error in browser → update allow_origins list in CORSMiddleware config
  - "Signature mismatch" on session → SESSION_SECRET env var changed between restarts

## ── SPRING JAVA MIGRATION PLAN ──────────────────────────────────────
Target: Spring Boot 3.3 + Java 21 (LTS)
Location: spring-backend/ directory
Build tool: Maven (pom.xml)
Key dependencies:
  spring-boot-starter-web          # REST controllers
  spring-boot-starter-data-jpa     # JPA/Hibernate ORM
  spring-boot-starter-validation   # Bean validation
  postgresql (driver)              # PostgreSQL JDBC
  spring-boot-starter-security     # CORS + security headers
  okhttp3 / spring-webclient       # HTTP clients for AI API calls
Migration order:
  Phase 1: Port all GET/health endpoints → Java controllers
  Phase 2: Port session management + database layer → JPA entities
  Phase 3: Port Stripe webhook handling (critical — verify signatures)
  Phase 4: Port AI story/image generation endpoints (largest)
  Phase 5: Port PDF generation (use iText or Apache PDFBox)
  Phase 6: Remove Python backend, update nginx config to port 8080
Java equivalent of Python env reading: @Value("${GEMINI_API_KEY}")
Java equivalent of pydantic model: Jakarta @Valid + record DTOs
Run Spring: mvn spring-boot:run -pl spring-backend (or java -jar target/*.jar)

## ── ORACLE CLOUD DEPLOYMENT ─────────────────────────────────────────
VM: Oracle Cloud Ampere A1 (ARM) or AMD E2 — Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
Open security list ports: 22 (SSH), 80 (HTTP), 443 (HTTPS), 5000 (dev)
iptables: sudo iptables -I INPUT 6 -m state --state NEW -p tcp --dport 5000 -j ACCEPT
Nginx config: reverse proxy 80/443 → localhost:5000 (Python) or :8080 (Java)
SSL: certbot / Let's Encrypt for HTTPS
Process manager: systemd service or PM2
Keep-alive SSH: ~/.ssh/config with ServerAliveInterval 60

Oracle VM start commands:
  # Python backend
  cd /home/ubuntu/Mathscript
  source venv/bin/activate
  uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5000

  # Spring Java backend (after migration)
  cd /home/ubuntu/Mathscript/spring-backend
  java -jar target/mathscript-backend.jar --server.port=8080

  # Build frontend
  cd /home/ubuntu/Mathscript/frontend
  npm install && npm run build

## ── ERROR DIAGNOSIS FLOWCHART ────────────────────────────────────────
When something is broken, check IN THIS ORDER:
1. Is the backend process running?           → ps aux | grep uvicorn
2. Is DATABASE_URL set?                      → echo $DATABASE_URL
3. Are all API keys set?                     → env | grep -E 'GEMINI|OPENAI|STRIPE|ELEVEN'
4. Is the frontend built?                    → ls frontend/dist/
5. Is nginx running (if production)?         → systemctl status nginx
6. Is port open in Oracle security list?     → curl http://localhost:5000/health
7. Check backend logs                        → journalctl -u mathscript -f
8. Check browser console for CORS errors
9. Check pydantic validation errors (422)
10. Check database connection logs

## ── CODE QUALITY STANDARDS ─────────────────────────────────────────
- No console.log in production frontend code (use observability.js)
- No print() in backend (use logger.warning/logger.error)
- All secrets from environment — never in source code
- Validate all user inputs at system boundaries
- Handle errors gracefully — never return raw exception messages to frontend
- Keep API response shapes consistent — frontend depends on exact field names
- Test all Stripe webhooks with Stripe CLI before deploying

## ── WHEN ASKED TO FIX A BUG ────────────────────────────────────────
1. Read the full error message and stack trace
2. Identify which layer failed (frontend/backend/DB/API/deploy)
3. Check the known issues list above first
4. Apply minimal fix — don't refactor unrelated code
5. Validate the fix won't break the other layer
6. Check env vars are correct for the environment
7. If unsure, add defensive logging, not blind try/catches

## ── WHEN ASKED TO ADD A FEATURE ─────────────────────────────────────
1. Read existing similar code in the codebase first
2. Follow existing patterns (state management, API client, backend models)
3. Add to backend/main.py endpoint + backend/database.py if DB needed
4. Add to frontend/src/api/client.js + relevant component
5. Keep React components focused — max ~200 lines, extract sub-components
6. Test with curl before wiring to frontend

## ── DO NOT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Do NOT add TypeScript (this project is intentionally JavaScript)
- Do NOT add Redux or heavy state management
- Do NOT use wildcard CORS in production
- Do NOT hardcode API keys, IPs, or secrets
- Do NOT use relative imports in backend (use `from backend.X`)
- Do NOT skip HMAC session verification
- Do NOT mix Python and Java backends simultaneously without nginx routing
